Honestly some of the worst logistics and restaurant layouts I have ever encountered. Be it, we went on New Year's Day, so it's busy... But the entire seating arrangement and process was a massive cluster. A plethora of people waiting for their tables block all the space for the wait staff, leave the door open letting the cold and just generally make it awkward to get around. To alleviate this human traffic jam, the host was atrocious at sitting people and turning around tables. She even gave our table away because she forgot what we looked like... but not to be petty the folks that got that table had to stand up and ask for service, so it kind of worked out. There a massive crowd of people waiting to sit, and there was multiple empty tables. On top of that, we witnessed multiple parties have to flag down staff to even get the most basic of service. So the atmosphere as a whole was  flat out uncomfortable.  Our actual waitress was fine, the food was very good, though the price point is quite high for the portions (I will always take issue with a side of toast being one piece of bread, if you charge me $15+ for omelette ya can toss another piece of bread in there).

This place is one of mine and my boyfriend's favorites. Their food is delicious. I've tried multiple things on their menu from their waffles to a few omelettes (the Cruz is my favorite) to their lunch items. No complaints on any. The staff isn't the friendliest but they're not mean either. They're always busy and running around like crazy so no hard feelings. They try their best to accommodate your needs and make small talk without taking up too much time. Although there's an older man who is at the register most of the time who I believe is the owner, don't think I've ever seen him smile nor does he seem very pleasant. It can get very full in the restaurant and the tables do seem a bit crammed. There is an outdoor seating area that is great if you're under the awning and not in the sun. They also have a bar. Throughout the years they have switched to a cash only restaurant which can be a little inconvenient when you're heading there for breakfast after not being awake long enough to brush your teeth (lol kidding!) let alone stop at the bank. However they do have an ATM there.  So all in all: - DELICIOUS food - Okay staff but grumpy owner - bring cash
